HEADWORD: Tweedledum and Tweedledee
<hw>Twee"dle*dum` and Twee"dle*dee`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>Two things
practically alike; -- a phrase coined by <person>John Byrom</person>
(1692-1793) in his satire ⟦ldquo⟧On the Feuds between Handel and
Bononcini.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

